      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@KJEjava48 Many ways to do it. The basic one is to create a new <code>Thread</code> class and either implement <code>run</code> on it or provide a <code>Runnable</code> instance to it, and then call <code>start()</code> on this <code>Thread</code> instance. In Kotlin there is a very short way to do it, using just <code>thread{ runCodeHere() }</code> ."
    } ],
