    "question_id" : 11411022,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Summarizing the solutions, I think that's the best one:</p>\n\n<pre><code>boolean isUiThread = VERSION.SDK_INT &gt;= VERSION_CODES.M \n    ? Looper.getMainLooper().isCurrentThread()\n    : Thread.currentThread() == Looper.getMainLooper().getThread();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And, if you wish to run something on the UI thread, you can use this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>new Handler(Looper.getMainLooper()).post(new Runnable() {\n    @Override\n    public void run() {\n       //this runs on the UI thread\n    }\n});\n</code></pre>\n"
