    "answer_id" : 57676093,
    "question_id" : 11411022,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Allow me to preface this with:\nI acknowledged this post has the 'Android' tag, however, my search had nothing to do with 'Android' and this was my top result. To that end, for the <strong>non-Android</strong> SO Java users landing here, don't forget about:</p>\n<pre><code>public static void main(String[] args)\n{\n    Thread.currentThread().setName(&quot;SomeNameIChoose&quot;);\n    /*...the rest of main...*/\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>After setting this, elsewhere in your code, you can easily check if you're about to execute on the main thread with:</p>\n<pre><code>if(Thread.currentThread().getName().equals(&quot;SomeNameIChoose&quot;))\n{\n    //do something on main thread\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>A bit embarrassed I had searched before remembering this, but hopefully it will help someone else!</p>\n"
